dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_3975  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Over-expressed GFP-tagged Rap2 in acute rat hippocampal slices is localized to dendrites and spines (Fig.1).\n\nThe use of constitute-active (ca) and a dominant-negative (dn) mutants of Rap2 indicate that Rap2 activity enhances synaptic depression (50% depressed AMPA-receptor-mediated responses in the Rap2(ca) mutant (Fig. C2), and potentiated AMPA responses in the Rap2(dn) mutant (Fig. 2 A, B)).\n\nRap2 activity further induces synaptic depotentiation which prevents the induction of LTP (Fig. 5) by mediating signalling that ultimately leads to the removal of synaptic GluR1- and GluR2L-containing AMPA receptors (Fig. 6).\n\n19/01/2021 Dnyanada: Rap2 mutant constructs, including the constitutively active mutant (G12→E), dominant-negative mutant (S17→N), and null/dead mutant (F39→S) were generated as described in Machida et al., 2004.\nLiteral:\ncDNA fragment encoding amino acids 1-168 of human Rap2A was subcloned into plasmid pBTM116 to yield pBTM116-Rap2A.\nP10114 (RAP2A_HUMAN) was chosen based on this.. Experimental description: Rap2 mutant constructs, including the constitutively active mutant (G12→E), dominant-negative mutant (S17→N), and null/dead mutant (F39→S; Machida et al., 2004), were generated using Quick Change Site-Directed mutagenesis kit (Stratagene, La Jolla, CA).\n\nMachida et al., 2004: A cDNA fragment encoding amino acids 1-168 of human Rap2A was subcloned into plasmid pBTM116 to yield pBTM116-Rap2A." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3975" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

